<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3206] Fix Visual Studio build failure due &apos;pthread_self&apos;: identifier not found</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3206</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Build fail of project lib\cpp\libthrift.vcxproj due to compile error&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;1&amp;gt;c:\...\thrift\lib\cpp\src\thrift\transport\tsslsocket.cpp(69): error C3861: &apos;pthread_self&apos;: identifier not found
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The current Thrift code calls &lt;a href=&quot;http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man3/pthread_self.3.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;pthread_self()&lt;/a&gt; which is not available on Windows platform in current Thrift library dependency set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Herein I propose resolution by using native WINAPI equivalent GetCurrentThreadId() in case source is compiled when _WIN32 macro is defined.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Visual Studio 2013 Update 5 RC&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
